      <notesStmt>
        <note rend="IDENTIFICATION">
          <p>Paris, Bibliothèque de l'Arsenal (Bibliothèque nationale de France), 3339</p>
        </note>
        <note rend="CONTENTS">
          <p><hi rend="italics">Roman de la Rose</hi> (ff. 1r-155v), <hi rend="italics">Le Testament</hi> (ff. 156r-185v), <hi rend="italics">Le Codicille</hi> (ff. 186r-186v), <hi rend="italics">Les Sept articles de la foi</hi> (ff. 187r-193r)</p>
        </note>
        <note rend="MATERIAL">
          <p>Parchment</p>
        </note>
        <note rend="ORIGIN">
          <p>France</p>
        </note>
        <note rend="DATE">
          <p>Beginning of the 15th century</p>
        </note>
        <note rend="SCRIPT">
          <p>Gothic, poem written in 2 columns of 36 lines</p>
        </note>
        <note rend="DECORATION">
          <p>1 double-column miniature in colors (containing 5 scenes: "L'Amans Sleeps," "L’Amans Dreams He Rises and Dresses," "L’Amans Goes into the Countryside," "L’Amans Approaches the River," "L'Amans at the Gate of the Garden of Deduiz"), with a full border of rinceaux, a bar border, and a large decorated initial (f. <locus>1r</locus>); miniature of Jean de Meun, with borders of rinceaux, a bar border, and a large decorated initial in colors and gold begin <hi rend="italics">Le Testament</hi> (f. <locus>156r</locus>); large decorated initial with borders of rinceaux and a bar border at the start of <hi rend="italics">Le Codicille</hi> (f. <locus>186r</locus>); miniature of Trinity, borders of rinceaux, a bar border, and a large decorated initial in colors and gold begin <hi rend="italics">Les Sept articles de la foi</hi> (f. <locus>187r</locus>). Smaller blue initials flourished in red and red initials flourished in blue throughout.</p>
        </note>
        <note rend="DIMENSIONS">
          <p>330 x 263 mm (this measurement is from Langlois)</p>
        </note>
        <note rend="FOLIATION">
          <p>ff. ii + 194 (this includes a blank at the end) + ii</p>
        </note>
        <note rend="BINDING">
          <p>French, 18th century; marbled brown calf, raised spine bands, stamped arms of Paulmy on spine, red leather spine label with gilt lettering, marbled endpapers.</p>
        </note>
        <note rend="PROVENANCE">
          <p>Bibliothèque de Paulmy, late 18th century; Bibliothèque de l'Arsenal, 19th century (after 1797).</p>
        </note>
        <note rend="NOTES">
          <p>Description of authors and manuscript written in an 18th-century hand on a flyleaf: <locus>frontmatter.flyleaf.02v</locus>
               </p>
        </note>
        <note rend="SELECT BIBLIOGRAPHY">
          <p>1. Henry Martin, <hi rend="italics">Catalogue des manuscrits de la bibliothèque de l'Arsenal</hi>, III, p. 337</p>
          <p>2. Langlois, <hi rend="italics">Les manuscrits</hi>, p. 78
               </p>
        </note>
        <note rend="N.B.">
          <p>This description has been compiled using the site's images and various published sources. If you have corrections or additional information on the manuscript, please do contact us.</p>
        </note>
        <note>
          <p>Description by Beatrice Radden Keefe</p>
